<TITLE> RAB arrest 7 robbers, seize microbus </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, May 25 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion (RAB) arrested seven robbers and seized a microbus and locally made arms from their possession at Savar in Dhaka early on Tuesday. The arrestees were identified as Jalilur Rahman, 37, Abul Kalam Azad, 28, Mizanur Rahman Mizan, 30, Mahbubur Rahman, 26, Zahurul Islam, 28, Faruk Hossain, 42, and Mansur Sheikh, 28. They were arrested in front of Chand Mia Market at Bhatpara of Savar. RAB produced the robbers before journalists at a press conference at its camp at noon. RAB-4 Savar Camp Commander squadron leader Shah Mizan-ul-Haque told journalists that RAB conducted a special drive at Bhatpara on the basis of secret information. They arrested seven robbers when they were preparing to go on a robbery. Haque said that the seized microbus (Dhaka Metro-Cha-13-5530) would be used for robbery. The law enforcers also seized three large choppers and 12 bamboo sticks from the microbus. A case was under way. bd
